org.apache.hc.client5.http.cache

Enum CacheResponseStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CacheResponseStatus>
      • org.apache.hc.client5.http.cache.CacheResponseStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<CacheResponseStatus>

    public enum CacheResponseStatus
extends Enum<CacheResponseStatus>
    This enumeration represents the various ways a response can be generated by the caching HttpClient; if a request is executed with an HttpCacheContext then a parameter with one of these values will be registered in the context under the key HttpCacheContext.CACHE_RESPONSE_STATUS.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CACHE_HIT
      A response was generated from the cache with no requests sent upstream.
      CACHE_MISS
      The response came from an upstream server.
      CACHE_MODULE_RESPONSE
      The response was generated directly by the caching module.
      FAILURE
      The response came from an upstream server after a cache failure
      VALIDATED
      The response was generated from the cache after validating the entry with the origin server.
